($$Kid Quest in Kensington Gardens, London: Superhero City Adventure for Kids (Ages 4–8)$$, $$Europe sculpture, Albert Memorial, London$$, null, 51.50223219999999, -0.1779626, $$Music & singing$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Europe%20sculpture%2C%20Albert%20Memorial%2C%20London$$, $$https://feverup.com/m/470942$$, null, null, 0, $$Recommended for families with kids between 4-8 years old ♿ Accessibility: Not suitable for people with reduced mobility Description Inspired by popular superhero teams, children will follow clues around the city, discover hidden places, and solve engaging puzzles with the help of their favorite animal heroes: a lion, panda, monkey, and labrador! Whether your child loves stories, solving mysteries, or simply exploring the world around them, this adventure will spark their imagination while you share meaningful time together outdoors! You walk to real locations in your city by following clues and once there, you will solve fun puzzles together and unlock new chapters$$, $$London$$, '{}', null, $$Select a live date and time on Fever before booking.$$, $$⭐ Turn your child into a superhero for a day! Kid Quest in London is a real-world city adventure for kids between 4 and 8 years old, designed to spark curiosity, connection, and learning through fun outdoor play. Highlights 🕵️‍♀️ A role-playing outdoor exploration game for designed kids aged 4-8 years old to explore the city in a safe and fun environment and learn about human senses while doing so! 💬 Co-created with a child therapist to encourage teamwork, critical thinking, and communication General Info 📅 Dates and times: select your date & time directly in the ticket selector ⏳ Duration: 40-60 mins 📍 Location: Europe sculpture, Albert Memorial, London 👤 Age requirement: Recommended for families with kids between 4-8 years old ♿ Accessibility: Not suitable for people with reduced mobility Description Inspired by popular superhero teams, children will follow clues around the city, discover hidden places, and solve engaging puzzles with the help of their favorite animal heroes: a lion, panda, monkey, and labrador! Whether your child loves stories, solving mysteries, or simply exploring the world around them, this adventure will spark their imagination while you share meaningful time together outdoors! You walk to real locations in your city by following clues and once there, you will solve fun puzzles together and unlock new chapters.$$, $$GBP 6.00 from Fever$$, true, $$Fever London family listings$$, $$https://feverup.com/m/470942$$, $$https://applications-media.feverup.com/image/upload/f_auto,w_720,h_720/fever2/plan/photo/b26cae00-984d-11f0-87de-8ac1fd8dec2d$$, $$https://feverup.com/m/470942$$, null, '{}'::date[], $$2026-07-11$$, null, '{}', $$date_range$$, $$Fever lists live availability in its ticket selector. Check Fever before booking.$$, $$published$$),
($$Harry Potter & the Cursed Child Parts One & Two$$, $$Palace Theatre, London$$, null, 51.5131866, -0.1294538, $$Parks & outdoor play$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Palace%20Theatre%2C%20London$$, $$https://feverup.com/m/110730$$, null, null, 0, $$suitable for 10+ How to use your tickets 1$$, $$London$$, '{}', null, $$Select a live date and time on Fever before booking.$$, $$📱 Smartphone tickets ⚡ Instant access to your tickets Highlights ⚡ Be enchanted by the magical Harry Potter universe ✨ A one-of-a-kind theatrical experience that has won rave reviews ✌️ Enjoy two incredible parts to the story The Show Come and enjoy the most awarded play in history during "one of the most defining pop culture events of the decade" (Forbes). There’s magic in every moment at Harry Potter and the Cursed Child and now, the eighth Harry Potter story is bringing the magic back to London’s West End in 2023. Nineteen years after Harry, Ron, and Hermione saved the wizarding world, they’re back on a most extraordinary new adventure – this time, joined by a brave new generation that has only just arrived at the legendary Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry. General Information 📅 Show timings: - Wednesday, Friday and Saturday: 2 PM - Sunday: 1 PM ⏱️ Duration: Part 1: 2hr 40min (incl 20min interval), Part 2: 2hr 35min (incl 20min interval) 👤 Age requirement: suitable for 10+ How to use your tickets 1. You'll instantly receive an email confirmation with your Harry Potter & the Cursed Child ticket. 2. Simply display the e-ticket on your mobile phone when arriving at the venue. Why choose Fever? ✔️ Millions of users book every month. ✔️ The best prices and availability at all times. ✔️ Thousands of unique experiences. ✔️ Verified user reviews. ✔️ 24/7 customer service. All ticket sales are final and cannot be refunded, exchanged, or otherwise modified. Click here to check out the T&Cs .$$, $$GBP 38.00 from Fever$$, true, $$Fever London family 